Some effective strategies for resolving conflicts peacefully include:
1. Establishing a respectful tone and setting;
2. Validating feelings of both parties; 
3. Making space to hear each other out; 
4. Identifying unhealthy patterns such as blaming or avoiding conflicts; 
5. Seeking help from a trusted third party when necessary; and 
6. Working towards win-win solutions that acknowledge and respect the needs of both parties, making sure to revisit plans if necessary until agreements are successful long-term goals.
